<!DOCTYPE html>
<!-- Important Note: Please edit the associated template file. The html file is generated automatically. -->
<html>
  <head>
<!-- begin: headPrelude -->
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta http-equiv='Content-Type' content='text/html;charset=UTF-8'/>

    <!-- prevent caching of html files to allow for session checks and transparent upgrades -->
    <meta http-equiv="Cache-Control" content="no-cache"/>
    <meta http-equiv="Pragma" content="no-cache"/>
    <meta http-equiv="Expires" content="0"/>

    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, user-scalable=no" />

    <meta name="apple-itunes-app" content="app-id=981727250" />


    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="favicon.01882ee1e5f3dc07a9f20581845c1585.ico">
<!-- end: headPrelude -->
<!-- begin: orcaBaseHelpers -->
    <script type="text/javascript">
        // "orca" is a global namespace for helpers that are needed before application load
        (function() {
            /*
            *  This function would load the UI5 jQuery programmatically.
            *  When the url query parameter consists of mobile-debug, it would load
            *  from absolutely path; otherwise, it would load from relative path because
            *  mobile has a cache proxy server to handle all the JS resources.
            *  Only use this function for mobile scenario.
            */
            function loadjQueryForMobile(fnOnSuccess) {
                var jQueryLibPath = orca.sapUi5Url + "/resources/sap/ui/thirdparty/jquery.js";
                if (orca.uriParams["mobile-debug"] !== "true") {
                    jQueryLibPath = "/" + jQueryLibPath;
                }
                orca.addScript(jQueryLibPath, function() {
                    fnOnSuccess();
                }, function() {
                   console.log("Failed to preload the Mobile jQuery Library");
                });
            };

            /*
            * This function loads the UIAssetsConfig from the Orca server.
            */
            function loadUIAssetsConfig() {
                function removeTrailingSlash(path) {
                    if (path[path.length - 1] === "/") {
                        return path.substring(0, path.length - 1);
                    } else {
                        return path;
                    }
                }
                if (sessionStorage && sessionStorage.orcaDevProxy) {
                    orca.uiAssetsPath = removeTrailingSlash(sessionStorage.orcaDevProxy);
                    if (orca.useNativeXhr) {
                        this._uiAssetsConfigPromise = new Promise(function (resolve, reject) {
                            resolve();
                        });
                        this._uiAssetsConfigPromise.finished = this._uiAssetsConfigPromise.finally;
                    } else {
                        this._uiAssetsConfigPromise = $.Deferred();
                        this._uiAssetsConfigPromise.finished = this._uiAssetsConfigPromise.always;
                        this._uiAssetsConfigPromise.resolve();
                    }
                } else if (orca.useNativeXhr) {
                    if (!this._uiAssetsConfigPromise) {
                        this._uiAssetsConfigPromise = new Promise (function (resolve, reject) {
                            var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
                            var url = "/sap/fpa/services/assets/getUIAssetsConfig.xsjs"
                            xhr.open('GET', url, true);
                            xhr.setRequestHeader("cache-control", "no-cache");
                            xhr.onload = function() {
                                var data;
                                try {
                                    data = JSON.parse(xhr.responseText || {});
                                } catch (err) {
                                    console.debug("Error parsing response json. " + err.message);
                                }
                                if (data.uiAssetsPath) {
                                    orca.uiAssetsPath = removeTrailingSlash(data.uiAssetsPath);
                                }
                                resolve(xhr);
                            }
                            xhr.onerror = function() {
                                console.log("Could not get the UI assets config! Falling back to default: '/sap/fpa/ui'");
                                reject(xhr);
                            }
                            xhr.send();
                        });
                        this._uiAssetsConfigPromise.finished = this._uiAssetsConfigPromise.finally;
                    }
                } else {
                    if (!this._uiAssetsConfigPromise || this._uiAssetsConfigPromise.state() === "rejected") {
                        this._uiAssetsConfigPromise = $.ajax({
                            url :  "/sap/fpa/services/assets/getUIAssetsConfig.xsjs",
                            type : "GET",
                            headers : {
                                "cache-control" : "no-cache"
                            }
                        }).done(function(data, textStatus, jqXHR) {
                            var data = data || {};
                            if (data.uiAssetsPath) {
                                if (data.uiAssetsPath.error) {
                                // just logging the error but still falling back to the default so as not to get in a bad state
                                    console.log("Could not get the UI assets config! Falling back to default: '/sap/fpa/ui'. The error was: " + data.uiAssetsPath.error);
                                } else {
                                    orca.uiAssetsPath = removeTrailingSlash(data.uiAssetsPath);
                                }
                            }
                        }).fail(function(jqXHR, textStatus, errorThrown) {
                            console.log("Could not get the UI assets config! Falling back to default: '/sap/fpa/ui'");
                        });
                    }
                    this._uiAssetsConfigPromise.finished = this._uiAssetsConfigPromise.always;
                }
                return this._uiAssetsConfigPromise;
            };

            /*
            * This function bundles preloading of both main and common chunks into one function call such that we could preload
            * on fallback as well.
            */
            function preloadMainChunks() {
                if (!orca.hasPreLoadedMainChunks) {
                    orca.storyPerfTimeStart("StoryPerformanceLogging - Load and compile main chunk");
                    orca.infraPerfTimeStart("InfraPerformanceLogging - Load and compile main chunk");
                    orca.preloadChunks(new RegExp("(\\.|\\_)main-chunk(?:(?!localization).)*\\.js$"));
                    orca.preloadChunks(new RegExp("(\\.|\\_)common-chunk(?:(?!localization).)*\\.js$"));
                    orca.preloadChunks(new RegExp("(\\.|\\_)firefly-runtime?.*\\.js$"));
                    orca.preloadChunks(new RegExp("(\\.|\\_)firefly-olap?.*\\.js$"));
                    orca.preloadChunks(new RegExp("(\\.|\\_)firefly-protocol?.*\\.js$"));
                    orca.hasPreLoadedMainChunks = true;
                }
            }

            /*
            * This function loads the Orca JS Entry Point for the HTML.
            * If the preloadChucks is supported, it would perform preloading orca resources.
            *
            * @param {object} opts
            * @param {boolean} [opts.preloadChunks=true] - whether to preload Orca main and common chunk are required
            * @param {boolean} [opts.redirectXSJSErrorPage=true] - whether to redirect to XSJS error page when loading of JS fails.
            */
            function loadJSEntryPoint(opts) {
                orca.getBuildManifest().finished(function() {
                    if (opts.preloadChunks) {
                        preloadMainChunks();
                    }
                    orca.addScript(orca.uiAssetsPath + "/" + orca.getBuildAsset(/^uiAssets[\\\/]app\.main\..*js$/), undefined, function onEntryPointError() {
                        console.log("Failed to load the app entry point: " + orca.uiAssetsPath);
                        // if there are issues with the uiAssetsPath then use the fallback uiAssets in HANA
                        // if there are issues with the fallback then display the error page
                        console.log("Attempting to load the fallback entry point.");
                        orca.uiAssetsPath = orca.uiAssetsFallbackPath;
                        var fallback;
                        if (orca.useNativeXhr) {
                            fallback = true;
                        }
                        orca.getBuildManifest(fallback).finished(function() {
                            if (opts.preloadChunks) {
                                preloadMainChunks();
                            }
                            orca.addScript(orca.uiAssetsPath + "/" + orca.getBuildAsset(/^uiAssets[\\\/]app\.main\..*js$/), undefined, function onEntryPointError() {
                                console.log("Failed to load the fallback entry point: " + orca.uiAssetsPath);
                                if (opts.redirectXSJSErrorPage) {
                                    window.location.href = "/sap/fpa/ui/public/error/unexpectedErrorPage.xsjs" + (orca.tenant ? "?tenant=" + orca.tenant : "");
                                }
                            });
                        });
                    });
                });

                if (opts.preloadChunks) {
                    // Preload localization chunk before app main js gets executed to improve loading time.
                    if (orca.useNativeXhr) {
                        Promise.all([orca.getBuildManifest(), orca.sessionPromise]).then(function(promiseResponses) {
                            var sessionLanguage = (promiseResponses) ? promiseResponses[1][0].session.language : "en";
                            var userLanguage = (sessionLanguage) ? sessionLanguage : "en";
                            orca.preloadChunks(new RegExp('(\\.|\\_)main-chunk_localization_' + userLanguage + '\\..*\\.js$'));
                            orca.preloadChunks(new RegExp('(\\.|\\_)common-chunk_localization_' + userLanguage + '\\..*\\.js$'));
                        }).catch(function(err) {
                            console.debug("Error resolving data for preload. " + err.message);
                        });
                    } else {
                        $.when(orca.getBuildManifest(), orca.sessionPromise).done(function(buildManifestPromiseResponse, sessionPromiseResponse) {
                            var sessionLanguage = (sessionPromiseResponse) ? sessionPromiseResponse[0].session.language : "en";
                            var userLanguage = (sessionLanguage) ? sessionLanguage : "en";
                            orca.preloadChunks(new RegExp('(\\.|\\_)main-chunk_localization_' + userLanguage + '\\..*\\.js$'));
                            orca.preloadChunks(new RegExp('(\\.|\\_)common-chunk_localization_' + userLanguage + '\\..*\\.js$'));
                        });
                    }
                }
            };


            /**
             * Returns a boolean to determine if remote debugging is used. If uiAssetsPath is orcadevproxy.sap.corp, remote debugging is
             * set to true. You can force remote debugging by adding &remoteDebug=true URL parameter.
             */
            function isRemoteDebugging() {
                if (orca.uriParams.remoteDebug === "false") {
                    return false
                } else {
                    return (orca.uriParams.remoteDebug === "true" || orca.uiAssetsPath.indexOf("orcadevproxy.sap.corp") !== -1);
                }
            }

            /*
            * This function loads the Orca CSS Stylesheets.
            * If the loading of the CSS requires to wait for the UI5 to finish loading, the loading of the CSS
            * would only happen after the UI5 is done; otherwise, the loading would start immediately.
            *
            * @param {object} opts
            * @param {boolean} [opts.waitForUI5=true] - whether to wait for UI5 to complete initialization.
            */
            function loadOrcaCSSStyle(opts) {
                function addOrcaCSS() {
                    /**
                     * Skip addOrcaCSS css for remote debugging. This is required because start-remote-debugging
                     * doesn't use ExtractCSS plugin.
                     */
                    if (!isRemoteDebugging()) {
                        orca.addStylesheet(orca.uiAssetsPath + "/" + orca.getBuildAsset(/^uiAssets[\\\/]app\.main\..*css$/), function onEntryPointError() {
                            console.log("Attempting to load the fallback css entry point.");
                            orca.uiAssetsPath = orca.uiAssetsFallbackPath;
                            orca.getBuildManifest().finished(function() {
                                orca.addStylesheet(orca.uiAssetsPath + "/" + orca.getBuildAsset(/^uiAssets[\\\/]app\.main\..*css$/));
                            });
                        });
                    } else {
                        console.log("Remote debugging detected. Skipping CSS entry point.");
                    }
                };

                if (opts.waitForUI5) {
                    sap.ui.getCore().attachInit(function() {
                        orca.getBuildManifest().finished(addOrcaCSS);
                    });
                } else {
                    orca.getBuildManifest().finished(addOrcaCSS);
                }
            };

            /**
             * Loads the SAP UI5 core scripts dependency. If sap-ui-debug=true is detected, load sap-ui-core-dbg.js.
             */
            function loadSapUi5Scripts(fnOnLoad, fnOnError) {
                orca.storyPerfTimeStart("StoryPerformanceLogging - Load UI5 core");
                orca.infraPerfTimeStart("InfraPerformanceLogging - Load UI5 core");

                var onLoadPerfTimeEndWrapper = function(fn) {
                    return function() {
                        orca.storyPerfTimeEnd("StoryPerformanceLogging - Load UI5 core");
                        orca.infraPerfTimeEnd("InfraPerformanceLogging - Load UI5 core");
                        fn();
                    };
                };

                var coreSapUi5File = (orca.uriParams["sap-ui-debug"] || "").toLowerCase() === "true" ? "sap-ui-core-dbg.js" : "sap-ui-core.js";
                orca.addScript(orca.sapUi5Url + "/resources/" + coreSapUi5File, onLoadPerfTimeEndWrapper(fnOnLoad), onLoadPerfTimeEndWrapper(fnOnError));
            }

            function getEmbeddedAppSessionPromise() {
                if (orca.useNativeXhr
                        && window.EmbeddedAppSession
                        && window.EmbeddedAppSession.getSession
                        && window.EmbeddedAppSession.getHeaders) {
                    var rawSession = window.EmbeddedAppSession.getSession();
                    var rawHeaders = window.EmbeddedAppSession.getHeaders();
                    if (rawSession && rawHeaders) {
                        try {
                            var session = typeof rawSession === "string" ? JSON.parse(rawSession) : rawSession;
                            var headers = typeof rawHeaders === "string" ? JSON.parse(rawHeaders) : rawHeaders;
                            return new Promise(function (resolve) {
                                var xhr = {
                                    status: 200,
                                    getResponseHeader: function(key) {
                                        return headers[key.toLowerCase()];
                                    }
                                }
                                resolve([session, 200, xhr]);
                            });
                        } catch (e) {
                            console.log("Failed to parse EmbeddedAppSession JSON object");
                        }
                    }
                }
                return null;
            }

            function loadUserSession() {
                // fire a request for session info as soon as possible so we are not blocked waiting for it later
                orca.infraPerfTimeStart("Load session");
                //for mobile, the csrftoken is retrieved from iOS native code,
                //iOS native pass the csrftoken in url parameter to vaoid csrftoke fetch from JS
                window.FPA_CSRF_TOKEN = orca.uriParams.fpaCsrfToken;
                var embeddedAppSessionPromise = getEmbeddedAppSessionPromise();
                if (embeddedAppSessionPromise) {
                    orca.sessionPromise = embeddedAppSessionPromise;
                } else if (orca.useNativeXhr) {
                    orca.sessionPromise = new Promise(function (resolve, reject) {
                        var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
                        var url = "/sap/fpa/services/rest/epm/session" + "?action=logon" + (orca.tenant ? "&tenantName=" + orca.tenant : "") +
                            (orca.urlRequestedLocale ? "&lang=" + orca.urlRequestedLocale : "") +
                            (orca.urlDataAccessLanguage ? "&dataAccessLanguage=" + orca.urlDataAccessLanguage : "");
                        xhr.open('GET', url, true);
                        xhr.setRequestHeader("X-CSRF-Token", window.FPA_CSRF_TOKEN ? window.FPA_CSRF_TOKEN : "Fetch");
                        xhr.setRequestHeader("X-Referrer-Hash", window.location.hash);
                        xhr.setRequestHeader("cache-control", "no-cache");
                        xhr.onload = function() {
                            var oSession = xhr.responseText;
                            try {
                                oSession = JSON.parse(xhr.responseText);
                            } catch (err) {
                                console.debug("Error parsing session JSON." + err.message);
                            } finally {
                                resolve([oSession, xhr.status, xhr]);
                                orca.infraPerfTimeEnd("Load session");
                            }
                        }
                        xhr.onerror = function() {
                            reject([xhr, xhr.status]);
                        }
                        xhr.send();
                    });
                } else {
                    orca.sessionPromise = $.ajax({
                        url :  "/sap/fpa/services/rest/epm/session" + "?action=logon" + (orca.tenant ? "&tenantName=" + orca.tenant : "") +
                        (orca.urlRequestedLocale ? "&lang=" + orca.urlRequestedLocale : "") +
                        (orca.urlDataAccessLanguage ? "&dataAccessLanguage=" + orca.urlDataAccessLanguage : ""),
                        type : "GET",
                        headers : {
                            "X-CSRF-Token" : window.FPA_CSRF_TOKEN ? window.FPA_CSRF_TOKEN : "Fetch",
                            "X-Referrer-Hash" : window.location.hash,
                            "cache-control" : "no-cache"
                        },
                        async : true
                    }).done(function(oSession, status, xhr) {
                        orca.infraPerfTimeEnd("Load session");
                    });

                }
            }

            function preloadSapUi5Styles() {
                // configure SAP UI5
                window["sap-ui-config"] = {
  "libs": "sap.ui.commons,sap.m,sap.ui.ux3,sap.ui.table,sap.ui.richtexteditor",
  "theme": "sap_belize",
  "language": "en",
  "resourceRoots": {
    "sap.fpa.sparca.ui": "/sap/fpa/services/dm/sparca/dataWrangler/js"
  },
  "preload": "async",
  "productive": true
};

                // preload ui5 library css files to speed up loading since they normally come in through XHR which is lower priority
                [
                    "/ui/core/themes/",
                    "/ui/layout/themes/",
                    "/ui/unified/themes/",
                    "/ui/commons/themes/",
                    "/m/themes/",
                    "/ui/ux3/themes/",
                    "/ui/table/themes/",
                    "/ui/richtexteditor/themes/"
                ].forEach(function(path) {
                    orca.addPreloadLink(
                        orca.sapUi5Url + "/resources/sap" + path + "sap_belize/library.css", "style", true
                    );
                });
            }

            var thirdPartyFiles = [
                "jquery-ui-core.js",
                "jquery-ui-widget.js",
                "jquery-ui-mouse.js",
                "jquery-ui-resizable.js",
                "jquery-ui-effect.js",
                "jquery-ui-sortable.js",
                "jquery-ui-draggable.js",
                "jquery-ui-droppable.js"
            ];

            function preloadThirdParties() {
                thirdPartyFiles.forEach(function(file) {
                    orca.addPreloadLink(
                        orca.sapUi5Url + "/resources/sap/ui/thirdparty/jqueryui/" + file, "script"
                    );
                });
            }

            function loadThirdParties(onLoadCallback) {
                var loadTP = function(files) {
                    if (files === undefined || files.length === 0) {
                        return onLoadCallback;
                    }

                    return function() {
                        orca.addScript(
                            orca.sapUi5Url + "/resources/sap/ui/thirdparty/jqueryui/" + files.shift(),
                            loadTP(files)
                        )
                    }
                };

                loadTP(thirdPartyFiles.slice())();
            }

            /**
             * This method will return locale code if it is passed in the URL using parameter named 'lang'.
             * Plus, it will check to see if it is within supported local. Otherwise, will return undefined.
             * @return {string} local code or undefined
             */
            function getUrlRequestedLocale() {
                var sLangCode;
                if (orca.uriParams["lang"]) {
                    var aAcceptedLang = [
  "ar",
  "bg",
  "zh_CN",
  "zh_TW",
  "hr",
  "ca",
  "cs",
  "cy",
  "nl",
  "da",
  "en",
  "en_GB",
  "fi",
  "fr",
  "fr_CA",
  "de",
  "de_CH",
  "el",
  "he",
  "hi",
  "hu",
  "id",
  "it",
  "ja",
  "ko",
  "ms",
  "no",
  "pl",
  "pt",
  "pt_PT",
  "ro",
  "ru",
  "sh",
  "sk",
  "sl",
  "es",
  "es_MX",
  "sv",
  "th",
  "tr",
  "uk",
  "vi",
  "en_US_sappsd"
];
                    if (aAcceptedLang.length > 0) {
                        var sRequestLang = orca.uriParams["lang"].toLowerCase().replace("-","_");
                        for (var i = 0; i < aAcceptedLang.length; i++) {
                            var sAcceptedLang = aAcceptedLang[i].toLowerCase();
                            if (sRequestLang === sAcceptedLang) {
                                sLangCode = aAcceptedLang[i];
                                break;
                            } else if (sRequestLang.indexOf("_") > 0) {
                                if (sRequestLang.substr(0, sRequestLang.indexOf("_")) === sAcceptedLang) {
                                    sLangCode = aAcceptedLang[i];
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }

                return sLangCode;
            };

            function getDataAccessLanguageFromURL() {
                var sDataAccessLanguage;
                var sReceivedDataAccessLanguage = orca.uriParams["dataAccessLanguage"] || orca.uriParams["lang"];
                if (sReceivedDataAccessLanguage) {
                    var reg = /^[a-zA-Z_]{2,14}$/;
                    sReceivedDataAccessLanguage = sReceivedDataAccessLanguage.replace("-","_");
                    var aMatchedDataAccessLanguageArray = sReceivedDataAccessLanguage.match(reg);
                    sDataAccessLanguage = aMatchedDataAccessLanguageArray? aMatchedDataAccessLanguageArray[0] : undefined;
                }
                return sDataAccessLanguage;
            }

            window.orca = {
                requestedEntryPoint: "mobile-loader",
                uriParams: {},
                tenant: undefined,
                buildManifest: {
                    assets: []
                },
                isRunningDevServer: false,
                uiAssetsPath: "/sap/fpa/ui",
                uiAssetsFallbackPath: "/sap/fpa/ui",
                supportedLocales: [
  "ar",
  "bg",
  "zh_CN",
  "zh_TW",
  "hr",
  "ca",
  "cs",
  "cy",
  "nl",
  "da",
  "en",
  "en_GB",
  "fi",
  "fr",
  "fr_CA",
  "de",
  "de_CH",
  "el",
  "he",
  "hi",
  "hu",
  "id",
  "it",
  "ja",
  "ko",
  "ms",
  "no",
  "pl",
  "pt",
  "pt_PT",
  "ro",
  "ru",
  "sh",
  "sk",
  "sl",
  "es",
  "es_MX",
  "sv",
  "th",
  "tr",
  "uk",
  "vi",
  "en_US_sappsd"
],
                getFormattedTime: function() {
                    var oDate = new Date();
                    return oDate.toLocaleTimeString() + "." + oDate.toISOString().slice(-4, -1) + " ms";
                },
                perfConsoleLog: function(message, appendTime) {
                    if ("sap-raptr-console" in orca.uriParams) {
                        console.log(message + (appendTime ? orca.getFormattedTime() : ""));
                    }
                },
                getSessionPerfLog: function(message, featureToggle) {
                    var featureOn = !featureToggle || orca.uriParams[featureToggle] === "true" || orca.uriParams["enableRAPTR"] === "true";
                    if (!featureOn) {
                        try {
                            featureOn = sap.fpa.ui.infra.common.FeatureToggle.isActive(featureToggle);
                        } catch(err) {
                        }
                    }
                    if (featureOn) {
                        if (window.sessionStorage && window.sap && sap.raptr) {
                            var duration = window.sessionStorage.getItem(message);
                            if (duration) {
                                sap.raptr.externalMeasure(message, duration);
                                window.sessionStorage.removeItem(message);
                                orca.perfConsoleLog(message + ": " + duration + "ms");
                            }
                        }
                    }
                },
